HEADWORD: Morulation
<hw>Mor`u*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>The process of cleavage, or segmentation, of the ovum, by which a
morula is formed.</def>⟦br⟧
